{
  "texts": [
    "ResultsOf the initial sample of 777,962 patients, only 109,556 had at least 2 visits more than 3 years apart and at least one note with social history.",
    "These patients had 375,334 notes with social history sections.",
    "After we applied pattern matching, 23,894 social histories were preselected for LLM processing.After 4 applications of the LLM on each social history, we deleted events outside of the screening interval.",
    "The mean time interval from the first visit to the screening was 4 years.",
    "This time interval was used on unscreened patients to similarly exclude events beyond the average time interval horizon to better balance screened and unscreened patients, as described in the Methods section.Manual verification of the events reduced the total number of correctly extracted events to 701 (Table 1)."
  ]
}